WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.480
It's not uncommon for us to teach the same course, but maybe with a few slight modifications.

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:13.840
Rather than creating the same course multiple times, we can actually reuse our RStudio Cloud

00:00:13.840 --> 00:00:16.520
workspace using one of two methods.

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:21.639
We can remove all of our learners once the course is completed and reuse the workspace,

00:00:21.639 --> 00:00:25.760
or we can copy the workspace for a new cohort of learners.

00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:30.959
To reuse our existing workspace by removing learners, we can go to the Members tab, located

00:00:30.959 --> 00:00:33.279
at the top of our workspace.

00:00:33.279 --> 00:00:38.939
From here, we can navigate to a specific member and click the Delete icon here.

00:00:38.939 --> 00:00:42.320
We can repeat this for any and all members in our workspace.

00:00:42.320 --> 00:00:47.240
However, if we'd like to remove large numbers of learners, we'll need to use the RSCloud

00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:48.240
package.

00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:53.919
It's also important to note that only admins can remove learners.

00:00:53.919 --> 00:00:57.799
This means that if you'd like any of your co-instructors or teaching assistants to help

00:00:57.799 --> 00:01:01.520
remove members from the shared workspace, they'll need to have their membership role

00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.799
switched to Administrator.

00:01:03.799 --> 00:01:07.639
Rather than remove learners, we can copy our workspace.

00:01:07.639 --> 00:01:13.000
Copying our workspace allows us to take all of the existing shared files to a new workspace

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.639
where we will be the only member.

00:01:15.639 --> 00:01:19.839
Just note that any private files in our workspace will not be copied over.

